    "LOMO stabilizes training through gradient clipping, a separate gradient norm calculation channel, and dynamic loss scaling.",
    "The integration of activation checkpointing and ZeRO optimization methods further reduces memory usage.",
    "Large AI model training and deploymentTraining of large AI models consists of four main components: dataset, algorithm architecture, computational re-sources, and deep neural network frameworks [152][153][154], as shown in Fig. 3.",
    "The quality, diversity, and scale of the dataset all have significant impacts on the model's performance and generalization ability.",
    "Large AI model training requires significant computational resources, including CPUs, GPUs, or dedicated accelerators (such as TPUs)."
